The paper focuses on developing a real-time programming and parameter reconfiguration method for autonomous underwater robots in human-robot collaborative tasks. This involves developing a gesture recognition framework using a convolutional neural network and a finite-state machine-based deterministic model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves developing a gesture recognition framework. The paper also discusses the usability of the proposed framework, indicating a focus on human-computer interaction, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of machine learning techniques for gesture recognition suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and robustness of the proposed framework, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
